{"lemma":"أَوّاب","slug":"أَوّاب","root":"#.#.ب","root_slug":"_-_-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/_-_-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أَوّاب","root":"أوب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":6},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1468"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%91%D8%A7%D8%A8"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to anger"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make shameful action toward"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʔaw.ʔa.ba/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1468","headword_ar":"اَوَّابٌ","root":"Awb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Frequent in returning."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Frequent in returning unto God, from one's sins;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wont to repent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"frequent in repenting:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, T, A, Mgh, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turning from disobedience to obedience:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or (S, L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a praiser of God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sa'eed Ibn-Jubeyr, TA;) by which is here meant, in the prayer of the period of the forenoon called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~uHaY","text_ar":"الضُّحَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", when the sun is high, and the heat violent; hence termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalaApu AlA^aw~aAbiyna","text_ar":"صَلَاةُ الاَوَّابِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; which is performed when the young camels feel the heat of the sun from the parched ground: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obedient:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Katádeh, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who reflects upon his sins in solitude, and prays God to forgive them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who keeps,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is mindful of, the ordinances prescribed by God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafiyZN","text_ar":"حَفِيظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which is thus explained by Bd and Jel as occurring in the Kur l. 31,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and does not rise from his sitting-place until he begs forgiveness of God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"('Obeyd Ibn-'Omeyr, T, TA: * [but this is evidently meant as an explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aw~aAbN","text_ar":"اَوَّابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"together with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafiyZN","text_ar":"حَفِيظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see the Kur ubi suprà:]) or one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who sins, and then returns to obedience, and then sins, and then returns to obedience."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Zj","T","A","Mgh","Msb","S","L","TA"]}]}}